parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty passenger airbag sensor can cause the airbag to malfunction, leading to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light comes on
indicating the airbag is off
even when an adult is sitting in the passenger seat. The light may turn off intermittently
and the problem may occur at different times
including when the passenger is seated before the car is started or when the passenger gets in the seat after the car is started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks while driving
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the check engine warning light illuminates
and the transmission fails to shift properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve body can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power or stalls
and the check engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to function
and the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dim or Inadequate Low Beam Headlights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim or inadequate low beam headlights can cause reduced visibility, making it difficult or impossible to see the road ahead, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Low beam headlights are extremely or dangerously low
headlights fail to adequately illuminate the roadway
visibility is limited
headlights are not bright at all
can't see two-three feet in front of the vehicle at night without high beams
blinker light is brighter than headlights
headlights are very
very dim
driving at night with low beam headlights is very
very dangerous.
